      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (scalar stress index, normalized index of hemolysis, pressure head) are directly linked to the clinical harm pathway for CPB hemolysis and to the regulatory decision question.",
      "rationale": "Scalar stress index and normalized index of hemolysis are established surrogates for red blood cell damage in CPB applications per ASTM F1841. Pressure head directly characterizes pump performance adequacy. Both QoIs map directly to the regulatory question of worst-case hemolysis operating condition identification."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
